T1  - Late-onset 3 beta-ol-hydroxysteroid-dehydrogenase deficiency: prevalence, clinical presentation and endocrine pattern.
A1  - Carmina, E
A1  - Rosato, F
A1  - Caputo, A
A1  - Janni, A
Y1  - 1985//
N2  - 3 patients with late-onset 3 beta-HSD deficiency are described. They presented increased DHEAs/delta 4 ratio either in basal conditions or after ACTH stimulation. All patients were hirsute but only one had increased serum values of delta 4 and total testosterone. However, all patients presented increased serum levels of free testosterone. Two patients had normal menstrual cycles and in one case a secondary PCO was found.
