T1  - Development of a low-dose monthly injectable contraceptive system: I. Choice of compounds, dose and administration route.
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.1016/s0010-7824(84)80029-3
A1  - Garza-Flores, J
A1  - Diaz-Sanchez, V
A1  - Jimenez-Thomas, S
A1  - Rudel, H W
Y1  - 1984//
N2  - A low-dose combined estrogen-progestogen sustained release system has been developed. The control of crystal size of the steroids produced sustained dissolution in vitro and in vivo. A dose-response experiment carried out in healthy women indicated that 10 mg of norethisterone (NET) with 1 mg of ethinylestradiol (EE2) when given by intramuscular injection maintained NET serum levels above 1 ng/ml for at least 25 days. The system is considered suitable for one month contraceptive protection.
