N2  - Data were compiled from 17 U.S. sites during a study of levonorgestrel, 0.15 mg, and ethinyl estradiol, 0.03 mg. A total of 1,130 women participated in 11,604 cycles of treatment. Efficacy, cycle characteristics, bleeding irregularities and side effects were studied. Weight and blood pressure means were analyzed with the paired t-test. Subject acceptance of this new combination oral contraceptive was high.
