T1  - Pelvic schistosomiasis and infertility.
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.1016/0020-7292(82)90072-8
A1  - El-Mahgoub, S
Y1  - 1982//
N2  - The use of laparoscopy allowed us to diagnose asymptomatic pelvic schistosomiasis in 13 infertile women. The lesion was associated with dense pelvic adhesions in all cases, a defective luteal phase in 23.1% of the women and anovulation in 15.4%. Atraumatic adnexolysis, antibilharzial treatment and correction of ovulatory defects were followed by intrauterine pregnancy in 46% of the patients.
