T1  - Monitoring of HMG-stimulated follicular development by real-time ultrasound.
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.1016/0028-2243(81)90022-8
A1  - Schmidt, W
A1  - Von Holst, T
A1  - Garoff, L
A1  - Gabelmann, J
A1  - Kubli, F
Y1  - 1981//
N2  - Monitoring of human follicular development by real-time ultrasound during HMG-HCG treatment is presented. With the aid of ultrasound monitoring, the ovulation rate is raised to 94.3% (formerly 80% without ultrasound). Serious side effects such as ascites and/or hydrothorax did not occur in this study (1.2% without ultrasound controls). The pregnancy rate was 21/47 (44%) of all hormonally treated patients. By means of real-time sector scan examination, the growing follicle could be detected in 103/106 (97.3%) of HMG-HCG treated cycles. Thus real-time ultrasound examinations provide results comparable to those achieved mostly by time-consuming compound scan in demonstration of the growing follicle.
