T1  - The infertile patient. Guidelines for successful workup.
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.1080/00325481.1980.11715632
A1  - Meeker, C I
Y1  - 1980//
N2  - The key to a successful infertility workup is to follow a protocol carefully and completely. After preliminary history taking and physical examination, tests are carried out systematically to investigate all possible ovulatory, cervical, tubal, and endometrial factors. A basal body temperature chart is essential for proper timing of tests, and a flow sheet helps keep track of results. Thorough evaluation of the man is also needed to identify possible causative factors.
