T1  - Ultrasonography of rapidly growing uterine leiomyomata associated with anovulatory cycles.
DO  - https://dx.doi.org/10.1148/radiology.134.3.7355223
A1  - Smith, J P
A1  - Weiser, E B
A1  - Karnei, R F Jr
A1  - Hoskins, W J
Y1  - 1980//
N2  - Three cases of rapidly growing leiomyomata uteri in young oligomenorrheic women are presented. The atypical ultrasonic and histologic findings are discussed. A spectrum of atypical ultrasonic findings including a high degree of transonicity and multiple areas of cystic degeneration is described. Histologic examination correlates well in explaining the sonographic characteristics. In addition, a possible relationship between the presumably anovulatory cycles present in these women and their rapidly growing leiomyomata is suggested.
