T1  - Role of the immune system in regulation of ovarian function-hypothesis.
A1  - Bukovsky, A
A1  - Presl, J
Y1  - 1978//
N2  - A hypothesis is presented on the interaction between the immune system and ovary in the regulation of the reproductive system and in the origin of some of its disorders. The cyclicity of ovarian function is considered to be primarily dependent on the induction of a specific cyclic immune response to the ovary. Similarly, the selection of a species-specific number of ovulating follicles during sexual maturity is thought to be ensured by immune mechanisms.
