T1  - [Induction of ovulation with Epimestrol (author's transl)].
T2  - Epimestrol--eine ovulationsauslosende Substanz
A1  - Benz, J J
A1  - Litschgi, M
Y1  - 1975//
N2  - Epimestrol 5 mg. daily for 10 days was administered in 119 treatment cycles to 21 women with normal gonadotropins and 33 ovulations were induced. Of the 21 patients, 7 had secondary amenorrhea, 10 had anovulatory oligomenorrhea and 4 had ovulatory oligomenorrhea. 17 patients desired pregnancies and 6 became pregnant. There was 1 pregnancy among 5 women with secondary amenorrhea. There were 3 pregnancies among 9 patients with anovulatory oligomenorrhea and 2 pregnancies in 3 patients with ovulatory oligomenorrhea. The pregnancy rate was 35%. Side effects were not observed.
