N2  - Synthetic LH-RH was used to induce ovulation and pregnancy in 6 women with suspected hypothalamic anovulation. The women had been previously treated with Clomid, but according to indirect evidence this drug either failed to induce ovulation or the women had insufficient luteal phase. After treatment with LH-RH one pregnancy occurred and in 3 more cases indirect evidence indicated that ovulation had occurred.
